      "message": "It\u0027s a little confused. On Mac, the handler receives the exception code from the OS, and the handler function is passed an exception_type_t (which is a Mach type), so that seemed to make sense there.\n\nOn Windows, it is indeed a DWORD as you point out. But the Windows exception handler reads the exception code by using the ExceptionSnapshot interface (which is cross-platform) https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/crashpad/crashpad/snapshot/exception_snapshot.h?q\u003dexceptionsnapshot+exception%5C(%5C)\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026l\u003d61\u0026dr\u003dC and so is a uint32_t rather than a DWORD.\n\nBut now that I look into that, it stores that return into an unsigned int, which seems wrong. So I changed all the return values from ExceptionHandlerServerException() to uint32_t.",
